HEADWORD: Cloakroom
<hw>Cloak"room`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A room, attached
to any place of public resort, where cloaks, overcoats, etc., may be
deposited for a time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

